project_descr: The project supports inclusive growth in Central Asia through the promotion of trade and enhancement of competitiveness, to support these countries’ efforts to reduce poverty and improve peoples’ lives.

outputs.output_descr: On regional level in Central Asia, trade policy makers are better equipped for dealing with regional trade issues; national export promotion agencies are cooperating regionally on regional exchange visits and coordinated marketing.

In Uzbekistan, trade policy makers are better qualified on easing trade with neighbouring countries, research and extension service providers are enabled to promote innovative trade approaches and sustainable ago-processing practices in Central Asia.

In Kyrgyzstan, trade-related policy makers are better qualified to support a favourable pro-poor trade promotion environment. Local authorities, selected business associations and service providers possess better capacities to promote pro-poor trade.

Facilitate development of trade policy docs, strengthen trade promotion institutes, promote sound business environment, ensure sustainable use of natural resources by selected agr value chains, support application of IT to improve business in Tajikistan.

project_title: aid for trade in central asia (aft phase iii)
